{
  "id": "019d36dd-59ee-7471-a325-dd266a92cffd",
  "content": "# Agent Teams Adapter Phase 1: Hook Scripts -- Decision Record (2026-03-28)\n\n## What\nImplemented 3 hook handlers (TaskCreated, TaskCompleted, TeammateIdle) + SessionEnd sweep + conditional hook registration for capturing Agent Teams coordination artifacts to staging.\n\n## Key Design Decisions\n1. **Rust handlers, not shell scripts**: Despite the issue referencing `.sh` scripts, implemented as native Rust handlers in `hooks/agent_teams.rs` to match the established pattern (session.rs, cleanup.rs). Shell scripts were the original approach but the codebase migrated to Rust handlers.\n2. **Dirs struct for testability**: Handlers accept a `Dirs` struct with injected paths, allowing tests to use temp directories without mutating HOME. Better than session.rs's free-function pattern.\n3. **Schema versioning from day 1**: All staging JSONL events include `\"v\": 1` for forward-compatibility. session.rs does this too; the 5-persona review caught the initial omission.\n4. **chrono for timestamps**: Used chrono (already a dependency) instead of hand-rolling date math. Produces millisecond-precision ISO 8601 timestamps consistent with session.rs.\n5. **PID-suffixed temp files**: atomic_copy uses `{name}.{pid}.tmp` to avoid collision when concurrent hooks copy the same target file.\n6. **umask before mkdir**: Set umask(0o077) before create_dir_all to avoid TOCTOU permission gap on staging directories.\n\n## Review Findings Worth Remembering\n- flock_append must flush the data file before the lock is released (explicit `file.flush()` + drop ordering comment)\n- `should_copy` should return false when source metadata fails (don't attempt to copy unreadable files)\n- `infer_team_from_task` must use `continue` on metadata failure instead of `?` which would abort the entire directory scan\n- Lock files (.lock) accumulate in staging -- Phase 2 adapter should clean them up\n\n## What Blocked / Surprised\n- Nothing blocked. The RFC was thorough and pre-reviewed.\n- The `TaskCreated` stdin not including `team_name` required the `infer_team_from_task` scan, which is the most complex logic in the module.",
